Python Strings

Strings are sequences of characters. Use single or double quotes.
Topics: indexing, slicing, len(), methods (strip, lower, upper, replace, split, ...),
concatenation, f-strings / format(), escape sequences (\n, \t, \\, \", ...).

Strings are immutable: methods return new strings.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_strings.asp
